## Important Rules

- **Coherent rubric across all four artifacts.** Same competencies, top to bottom. This is THE rule that determines whether the loop actually works.
- **Don't back-fit.** Generate the kit BEFORE you have a candidate in mind. Otherwise you'll bias the rubric.
- **Independent scoring before debrief.** Anchoring is the #1 way hiring loops fail.
- **Veto is real.** Strong-no from any interviewer means stop. Don't override.
- **Feedback in 5 days, win or lose.** Candidate experience is a recruiting funnel.
- **No surprise stages.** Every stage is in INTERVIEW.md. Add only with the candidate's consent and time-cost honored.
- **Compensation band is part of the JD.** Posting without it wastes everyone's time.
